## What to do
The ATProto site records store the shapefile field as a SmallBlob wrapper object:
```json
{
  "$type": "org.hypercerts.defs#smallBlob",
  "blob": {
    "$type": "blob",
    "ref": { "$link": "bafyrei..." },
    "mimeType": "application/geo+json",
    "size": 12345
  }
}
```

But fetchSiteShapefile (line ~43) checks for `shapefile.ref?.$link` — the BlobRef is nested under `.blob`, not at the top level. All three cases in the function fail and it returns null, so no polygon is drawn and the map never zooms.

### Fix
At the top of fetchSiteShapefile, before the existing case checks, unwrap the SmallBlob wrapper:

```ts
// Unwrap SmallBlob / SmallImage wrapper if present
// ATProto site records wrap the BlobRef in { $type: '...', blob: <BlobRef> }
let resolvedShapefile = shapefile;
if (
  typeof shapefile === 'object' &&
  shapefile !== null &&
  'blob' in shapefile
) {
  resolvedShapefile = (shapefile as Record<string, unknown>).blob;
}
```

Then use `resolvedShapefile` instead of `shapefile` in all the subsequent checks (the isBlobRef case, the string cases, etc.).

